dct_description_sm: Map of German South West Africa [Namibia] showing German, British and Portuguese interests, the boundaries of the major local and tribal chiefs in the German protected areas, military posts, Protestant and Roman Catholic mission stations, bodies of water and routes of travellers (James Alexander, Charles John Andersson, J. Böhm and F. Bernsmann, Hermenegildo de Brito Capello and Roberto Ivens, James Chapman, Charles Duparquet, Edward Fleck, Curt Karl Bruno von François, Georg Gürich, Carl Hugo Hahn and Johannes Rath, Jan Christiaan Smuts, and Francis Christian Ludwig von Steinäcker).
Relief shown by hachures, shading and spot heights.
Bar scale on map given in "Kilometer."
Index, legend, and descriptive text at bottom left.

Top left: "Richard Kiepert, Deutscher Kolonial-Atlas"; top right: "No. 3"; lower left: "Abgeschlossen 15. October 1892"; lower right: "Lith. Anst. v. Leop. Krantz, Berlin". Appears in Richard Kiepert and Joseph Partsch's Deutscher Kolonial-Atlas für den amtlichen Gebrauch in den Schutzgebieten. Berlin : Reimer, 1893. Inset lower left: [Eastern continuation of upper portion of map]. Note on map at point of continuation: "Östliche fortsetzung sin der ecke unten links."
Inset map: [Eastern continuation of upper portion of map]. Note on map at point of continuation: "Östliche fortsetzung sin der ecke unten links."
Richard Kiepert and Joseph Partsch's Deutscher Kolonial-Atlas für den amtlichen Gebrauch in den Schutzgebieten. Berlin : Reimer, 1893.
